                <created>Fri, 3 Jan 2014 11:07:57 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 16 Apr 2019 09:31:56 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 8 Jan 2014 16:25:29 +0000</resolved>
                                        <fixVersion>1.2.14</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13861961" author="kmueller" created="Fri, 3 Jan 2014 22:26:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We were also bit by this in my duplicate issue 6549&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863210" author="alexliu68" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 18:38:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lift both EACH_QUORUM and LOCAL_QUORUM. Cast strategy to NTS only if it&apos;s an instance of NTS, otherwise don&apos;t cast it and use it the same way as QUORUM.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863575" author="j.casares" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:51:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m also sometimes seeing this in 2.0.4 while testing the java-driver. If I try and rerun the test that fails by itself it will pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13865595" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 8 Jan 2014 16:25:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The changes looks good, though one problem remained in that DatacenterSyncWriteResponseHandler, used by EACH_QUORUM, was still asserting NetworkTopologyStrategy. Anyway, it&apos;s simple enough to just fallback on the simple WriteResponseHandler with SimpleStrategy so committed with that added (and a few minor cosmetic change to the original patch). Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
